Brydge Triumphs in Red Dot Award & Continues to Amass Fans
[May 03, 2016]
Brydge Triumphs in Red Dot Award & Continues to Amass Fans
Tweet
PARK CITY, Utah, May 3, 2016 /PRNewswire/ --Brydge, the company that has set a new benchmark for iPad keyboards, announces that it has been awarded a Red Dot Design Award for excellence in design for the BrydgeAir keyboard for iPad Air 1 & 2 and 9.7 inch iPad Pro.
"Beautifully designed products which also provide maximum functionality is our core product philosophy at Brydge," said Nicholas Smith, CEO of Brydge. "The Red Dot Award recognizes our continual drive to produce the most beautifully designed accessories on the market."
Providing the perfect complement to the iPad, Brydge has engineered its keyboards to maximize the functionality of the tablet while providing the productivity of a MacBook. Award-winning features include Brydge's patented 180-degree hinge ystem, high-grade 100 percent aluminum build, backlit keys and superb MacBook-like typing experience.
The Red Dot Award comes on the heels of Brydge's recent CES 2016 Innovation Awards Honoree win for the BrydgeMini for iPad mini 1, 2 & 3 as well as the GottaBeMobile Excellent Award for the BrydgePro for 12.9 inch iPad Pro at CES 2016.
Founded in 1954, the Red Dot Award: Product Design competition appraises the best products of the year from all over the world.Honoring a select group of products out of the thousands entered each year, Red Dot winners are chosen by an international jury who seeks to find products that significantly stand out for having exceptional design.
About Brydge
Brydge has redefined the standard for tablet keyboards. Starting out with one of the most successful Kickstarter campaigns of 2012, Brydge now has customers in over 180 countries and established a core foundation for rapid growth. Brydge keyboards are consistently rated as the leading iPad keyboard on the market. Brydge has a vision to become the global leader in premium mobile and detachables accessories. For more information about Brydge and its products, please visit www.brydgekeyboards.com or connect with Brydge on Facebook (www.facebook.com/brydgekeyboards/) or Instagram (https://instagram.com/brydgekeyboards/) or Twitter (https://twitter.com/brydgekeyboards.
Brydge is a trademark owned by Brydge and may be registered. All other trademarks are the property of their respective owners.
Logo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20151110/285991LOGO
